culations and video game fantasies into reality. Milburn suggests that the closing of the gap between bits and atoms entices scientists, geeks, and gamers to dream of a completely programmable future. Welcome to the wild world of Mondo Nano.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aGames and technology. 0aGamesxSocial aspects. 0aNanotechnologyxSocial aspects. 7aCOMPUTERS / Social Aspects / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071182040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822376330zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822376330423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822376330.jpg  a978-3-11-071182-0  DUK eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles